 - **Optional automation**:
   - Use GitHub Actions to trigger a backup tag on successful PR to `main` with `#backup` label
 
+## ­ƒñû Automation
+
+Backups can be run locally via `sprint_release.py` or via GitHub Actions (manual or on PRs labeled `backup`).
+
+### Local Execution
+
+Run the sprint release script from the repository root:
+
+```bash
+# Full backup with smoke test and SSOT validation
+python ops/scripts/sprint_release.py --tag "v5.4-sprint15-complete" --desc "Sprint 15 completion milestone"
+
+# Skip smoke test if backend is down
+python ops/scripts/sprint_release.py --tag "v5.4-sprint15-complete" --desc "Sprint 15 completion milestone" --skip-smoke
+
+# Skip SSOT validation
+python ops/scripts/sprint_release.py --tag "v5.4-sprint15-complete" --desc "Sprint 15 completion milestone" --skip-validate
+```
+
+### GitHub Actions
+
+The workflow can be triggered:
+- **Manually** via GitHub Actions UI with custom tag and description
+- **Automatically** when a PR is merged with the `backup` label
+
+Artifacts (smoke test JSON and SSOT validation output) are automatically uploaded and attached to the GitHub Release.
+
 ---
 
